text: Selwyn Kole (born 26 December 1973) is a retired middle distance athlete from the Solomon Islands. Kole represented the Solomon Islands team that compete at the 1996 Summer Olympics which was held in Atlanta. He entered the 1500 metres, he finished 12th in his heat so didn't advance to the next round.Sports Reference Profile In 1995 he competed at the 1995 World Championships in Athletics held in Gothenburg, he finished last in his heat. ==References== Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:People from Guadalcanal Province Category:Solomon Islands male middle-distance runners Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic athletes of the Solomon Islands Category:World Athletics Championships athletes for Solomon Islands
